Description: Papyrus: three fragments of administrative register entries; Demotic text. Fragment A has Hieratic text, with two columns of Demotic below--register entries of administrative documents, including one dated to Yr. 10 of Ptolemy. Frag B includes Greek names in Demotic. Frag C refers to vacant lands
Curator's comments: To be published by Kim Ryholt ('another papyrus from Tebtunis (an account written partly in hieratic > and partly in demotic, and dated to the reign of Cladius), and I've > just discovered that it joins P. Carlsberg 566.)
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (381093) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/381093)
